  "text": "Nothing beats the magic of a winter holiday in the mountains. Whether you’re skiing or snowboarding in the Alps, husky-sledding through frozen forests in Scandinavia, snowshoeing in Poland’s Tatra mountains, or simply soaking up the snowy splendour from the hot tub of a mountain hideaway in the Dolomites, we’d love to hear about your favourite winter getaways in Europe.If you have a relevant photo, do send it in – but it’s your words that will be judged for the competition.Keep your tip to about 100 wordsThe best tip of the week, chosen by Tom Hall of Lonely Planet, will win a £200 voucher to stay at a Coolstays property – the company has more than 3,000 worldwide. The best tips will appear in the Guardian Travel section and website.We’re sorry, but for legal reasons you must be a UK resident to enter this competition.The competition closes on 21 October at 9amHave a look at our past winners and other tipsRead the terms and conditions hereSend us your travel tipsShare your tips with us by filling in the form below.Please share your story if you are 18 or over, anonymously if you wish. For more information please see our terms of service and privacy policy.Your responses, which can be anonymous, are secure as the form is encrypted and only the Guardian has access to your contributions. We will only use the data you provide us for the purpose of the feature and we will delete any personal data when we no longer require it for this purpose. For true anonymity please use our SecureDrop service instead.Enter your tip (maximum 100 words), including details of location, price and website Add a photograph if you wish (but it's the words we'll be judging) OptionalPlease note, the maximum file size is 5.7 MB.Choose fileYour name First name only if you preferWhere do you live? This competition is only open to UK-based readersEmail address By submitting your response, you are agreeing to share your details with us for this feature.",
